datastructures.symbol_tables

Class OrderedST<Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>,Value>

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.symbol_tables.ST<Key,Value>
      • datastructures.symbol_tables.OrderedST<Key,Value>
  • Type Parameters:
    Key - The type for the key member in the pairs of this symbol table.
    Value - The type for the value member in the pairs of this symbol table.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BSTOrderedST, DualArrayOrderedST

    public abstract class OrderedST<Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>,Value>
extends ST<Key,Value>

    OrderedST is an ordered symbol table ADT. An ordered symbol table induces a partial ordering among its keys, and this is the reason for which we've made keys Comparable in this interface. Ordered symbol tables provide for a richer interface than classic symbol tables, as suggested by the key ordering.

    Since:
    October 2013
    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
